author: @coreyms
text: Hey everyone! Thanks for being so patient while I finished this course! I am still finishing the last few videos of the course and have many more to record, but I am hoping to release Part 2 tomorrow. The next video will cover DataFrame and Series datatypes. These datatypes are the backbone of Pandas and learning what they are and how to use them is essential, so be sure to check that out.  I'd like to thank Brilliant for sponsoring this series. If you'd like to check them out then you can sign up with this link and get 20% off your premium subscription: https://brilliant.org/cms

author: @KrishNa-hm8mk
text: For those who installed *Python 3.8* : If you getting errors when running *pip install jupyterlab* , try running *pip install --upgrade setuptools* first. This will update the tools needed to run jupyter like Microsoft Visual C++ 14. After this, run the install command. If you are getting *NotImplemented* error while launching jupyter notebook using the command jupyter notebook, checkout the first answer in the following Stack Overflow link and apply it. It will work fine after this fix. https://stackoverflow.com/questions/58422817/jupyter-notebook-with-python-3-8-notimplementederror
